        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-15 10:20:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nAs previously mentioned, please do not mix up different changes in the same patch.  This patch has a description for \"fix autogen with modern autoconf tools\", but there is a LOT of change in this patch that has nothing at all to do with autoconf.  All of the portability fixes should go into a separate patch, along with a clear description of what is being done.\n\nI stated my reasons for this very clearly in the previous inspection for patch set #4.\n\nUnfortunately, patch set #7 (with only the autoconf changes) was ready to land, but has now been clobbered by a patch that is not going to land as it currently stands.  You could have based the additional compatibility changes on top of patch set #7.\n\nIf you have some disagreement with the inspection, please reply to the comments with your reasoning.  Do not just ignore the inspection comments.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
