        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-06-27 17:54:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nYou can make 2 patches that are dependent. \n\nMaybe one patch has the fixes you need and the 2nd patch is the generic autoconf changes. \n\nThe idea of one basic group of changes per patch allows for better review of the patch.  Right your patch is titled fix autogen and that is what your commit message says but then it goes off and does a great many other things.  I don't doubt these other changes are needed but you can put them into a separate patch so they can be properly reviewed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
